{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c53bb2d7-8958-47c0-8c69-375774506d1e","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n1. **Update NUnit3TestAdapter** to **v5.0.0+** — it includes the Microsoft.Testing.Platform support.\n\n2. **Remove** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` from your project references.\n\n3. **Add an MSBuild property** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Enable the test runner** (choose one):\n   - **Preferred:** Add the property `<GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>true</GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>` to your `.csproj`.\n   - **Alternative:** Create a `Program.cs` entry point manually using `Microsoft.Testing.Platform.Builder`.\n\n5. Run tests with `dotnet test` as before — it now routes through Microsoft.Testing.Platform instead of VSTest.\n\n**Optional but recommended:** Add `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` so the test project produces a directly runnable executable.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2032de5b-8165-4bda-9e38-ea80a4dfd5d1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I can answer it directly without needing to explore any codebase.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about the migration steps.","outputTokens":343,"requestId":"4C16:3F94EE:D6CC56:10A6514:6A0128B7"},"id":"af43bd3b-ee74-4afc-a0bb-3dab26ab306c","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:54:23.744Z","parentId":"a5992ba1-192a-44db-8dd8-2db1552c011d"}
